08/08/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- An informal meeting of the defence ministers of NATO member states will take place in Poiana Brasov, Romania, from 13 October to 14 October, the Romanian government said in a statement Friday (6 August).
The event is expected to focus on international security and the training of the new Iraqi security forces.
An informal NATO-Russia meeting is also on the agenda.
This will be the first high-level meeting of the Alliance since the Istanbul summit took place in June.
(Nine O'Clock - 06/08/04)
